{
  "texts": [
    "Two operations are defined on p-sites, the Knit and the Nerve.",
    "The Knit maps a p-site to a p-formation with the same base, the Nerve maps a p-site to a p-structure with the same base.",
    "In the opposite direction, the canonical map associates to any p-formation a canonical p-site.",
    "It turns out that the Knit map establishes a bijection between canonical p-sites and p-formations the inverse of which is precisely the canonical map.",
    "On the other hand the Nerve map establishes a bijection between the set of perfect canonical p-site and the set of p-structures (simplicial complexes)."
  ]
}